<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/general-requirements.aspx">Back to Eligible Income</a></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Salary Sacrifice Arrangements (General):</b></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Salary sacrifice is an arrangement between an employer and an employee, whereby the employee agrees to forgo part of their  salary or wages in return for the employer providing them with benefits of a similar value.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">A salary sacrifice arrangement is also commonly referred to as <b>salary packaging</b> or <b>total remuneration packaging</b>.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Novated Lease</b><br/> For novated leases, refer to the <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/sal-sac-novated-lease-p1t0.aspx" target="_blank">Salary Sacrifice (Novated Leases) page. </a></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>FBT ‘Tax Free’ Salary Sacrifice:</b><br/> For customers employed by a FBT exempt employer who want their pre-tax salary sacrifice amount to be treated as ‘tax-free’, refer to the <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/credit-policy/eligible-income/sal-sac-fbt-exempt-p1t0.aspx" target="_blank">Salary Sacrifice (FBT Exempt Employers) page. </a></span></p>
</div>
